-- TAKE A LOOK-G20 finance ministers and central bankers meet in Australia
-- 
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 02:43AM EDT
-- None



Sept 19 (Reuters) - G20 host Australia is leading a push to draw a line under the global financial crisis, urging the group of top economies to swiftly finalise regulations aimed at preventing a repeat of the crash and focus on measures to revive sputtering global growth.

